{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"Included with: <b> ἀμπλᾰκ-εῖν</b>, <br /> <i>infinitive</i> of <i>aorist</i> ἤμπλακον (ἤμβλακον[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 7th c.BC: Archilochus Lyricus 73, 6th c.BC: Ibycus Lyricus 24), \">Refs 7th c.BC+</a>]<i>participle</i> ἀμπλ- and ἀπλ-ακών (see. below): <i>perfect</i> <i>passive</i> ἠμπλάκημαι[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Supplices” 916\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>present</i> only later ἀμπλακίσκω, <i>Doric dialect</i> ἀμβλακίσκω [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Theages Philosophus cited in 5th c.AD: Stobaeus, Joannes 3.1.117\">Refs 5th c.AD+</a>]: <i>Doric dialect</i> <i>imperfect</i> ἀμβλάκισκον[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Phintys Pythagoreus cited in [same work] 4.23.61 (ἀμβλακεύω\">Refs</a>] is variant for{βλακεύω} in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ ἄρθρων ἐμβολῆς” 17\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; compare βλάξ): <br /><Level2><b>__I</b></Level2> with <i>genitive</i>, <b>miss, fail</b> or <b>come short of,</b> ἀνορέας οὐκ ἀμπλακών[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “O.” 8.67, compare 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Antigone” 554, 1234. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__I.2</b></Level3> <b>lose, be bereft of,</b> εἰ τοῦδ᾽ ἤμπλακον (i.e. παιδός)[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. work] 910; νόστου 4th-5th c.BC: Simonides Lyricus 119; ἀρίστης ἀπλακὼν ἀλόχου 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Alcestis” 242; λέκτρων ἀπλακών [prev. author] “IA” 124. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <i>absolutely</i>, <b>do amiss, sin, err,</b> παρ θεοῖς[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 6th c.BC: Ibycus Lyricus 24, compare 7th c.BC: Archilochus Lyricus 73, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hippolytus” 892, “Andr.” 948, etc.: with _neuter_ pronoun, ὡς τάδ᾽ ἤμπλακον\">Refs 7th c.BC+</a>] when <b>I committed</b> these <b>sins,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 1212\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, τί δ᾽ ἠμπλάκηται τῶνδέ μο;[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Supp.” 916.—Not in 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] <b>ἀμπλᾰκ-ημα</b>, τό, <b>error, fault,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 112, 388, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Antigone” 51, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]—poetical and late Prose, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.226e, 2nd c.AD(?): Theodotion LXX.Dan.6.4\">LXX+1st c.AD+</a>]:—for the sake of meter, ἀπλάκημα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Eumenides” 934.\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G6264","accentedUnicode":"ἀμπλάκημα","shortDef":"an error","mediumDef":"an error","stepGloss":"an error","stepTransliteration":"amplakēma","count":0,"_step_Type":"word"}]}